cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based interactive segmentation method for medical images, which involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and geodesic distance transforms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a resolution-preserving network and integrates user interactions as hard constraints into a back-propagatable Conditional Random Field, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper deals with medical images, which could also suggest cs.MM (Multimedia) as a possible category. Finally, the use of CNNs and geodesic distance transforms for segmentation could also suggest cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category.
